manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: ATX 3.0 COMPATIBLE It has an output port that is compliant with PCIe 5.0 and Intel PSDG(Power Supply Design Guide) ATX 3.0, also the MAG A850GL PCIE5 power supply can handle up to 2x total power excursion and 3x GPU power excursion.
DUAL-COLOR 16-PIN CABLE Our award-winning yellow 16-pin PCIe cable easily shows users if the cable has been plugged in properly.

80 PLUS GOLD CERTIFIED The efficiency of your power supply directly influences your system’s performance and your power consumption. The 80 PLUS Gold certification promises lower energy consumption and higher efficiency.
DC TO DC & FULL BRIDGE A Full bridge DC to DC design achieves higher conversion efficiency, stabler output voltage, and quicker voltage adjustment for different usage scenarios.
FLUID DYNAMIC BEARING The power supply’s fan sports a fluid dynamic bearing that perfectly balances cooling performance and noise level.

FLAT BLACK CABLES The flat cables make cable management easier and less of headache! Thanks to the flat cables, the entire system can be more organized and has more room for unobstructed airflow. FULL MODULAR DESIGN The connectors that required by the build need to be used, significantly reducing cable clutter and simplifying the system’s overall build. COMPACT SIZING Smaller than typical PSUs on the market, this power supply unit that can save space and make it easier to organize cables in the computer case by freeing up more room inside.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It works well
reviews.reviewText: Computer power supplies units are meant to be invisible. If you are thinking about your PSU; something is not right. This PSU is silent, has great performance number, and the monitoring tools I used says it is producing smooth steady power. It is just there doing a great job keeping the computer running well so I can focus on other things. The modular nature of the cables made installation a breeze.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars An Amazing Power Supply Unit
reviews.reviewText: I really like that MSI has gotten into the power supply unit manufacturing side of computer hardware. This power supply is very compact, quiet and has enough power to run everything that I have thrown at it in my hardcore gaming build. One of the best features of MSI is that they use factory seal stickers that can only be removed once on all of their hardware so there is no chance you are receiving someone else's damaged store return when buying from online/ box stores that sometimes will not admit that they resell returned items which they sometimes do. This MSI power supply unit is exactly what I needed for my computer needs of cable modularity and for future component upgrades that may carry a need for increased overall wattage. It delivers beyond expectations on every level. One of my favorite features is the sweet looking logo imprinted onto the power supply unit that enhances the aesthetics of my build. I wanted to try to find one thing about this product that I didn't like but I honestly cant as this is a job well done. Great job MSI, my favorite go to brand!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great compact and budget PSU
reviews.reviewText: This power supply is compact and user-friendly, providing all the necessary cables. The inclusion of a colored 16-pin PCIe cable adds a reassuring element, ensuring a secure connection when plugging in your VGA. The fan is quiet and only turns on when your computer is working hard, like during gaming. I recommend it if you're looking for an affordable and compact power supply.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Excellent PSU that fits practically any case.
reviews.reviewText: This is an outstanding PSU for the money. It is extremely quiet and has plenty of modular cables included and even a bag to store the ones you don’t use. Comes with one PCIe5 cable, ATX connector, two CPU cables, two PCIe cables, an SATA cable, a molex cable and is ATX 3.0 ready. The ONLY reason I took off 1 star is that the 24pin ATX connector has to stretch oddly to fit into the PSU, you almost feel like your going to break the cable the way you have to twist it to fit into the PSU. The same connector is also tough to fit into the motherboard. It feels like it just doesn’t make a good connection or snap in. I’ve installed 3 of them, 2 connected to a ASUS motherboard and 1 used on a MSI motherboard, and it was the same feeling trying to make the connector fit. One of the computers wouldn’t turn on one day and I took the connector off the motherboard and plugged it back in. It still didn’t work, then I twisted the cable a little bit and the computer started up. I would buy another for $100.
